{"lemma":"حَجِّ","slug":"حَجِّ","root":"ح.ج.ج","root_slug":"ح-ج-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ج-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَجّ","root":"حجج","pos":"N","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7106","n7112","n7113","n7253"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to overcome, defeat, defend (with arguments, evidence, etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to convince"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make a pilgrimage"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make a pilgrimage; to perform the hajj (make a pilgrimage to Mecca according to a specific ritual)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go towards, visit, repair to (obsolete)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَجَّ (ḥajja) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pilgrimage","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pilgrimage; hajj (pilgrimage to Mecca according to a specific ritual)","tags":["uncountable"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew חַג (ḥaḡ, “feast-day”), Classical Syriac ܚܓܐ (ḥaggā, “feast”), Classical Syriac ܚܳܓ (ḥāgg, “to go around”), Ge'ez ሕግ (ḥəgg, “law”), Ge'ez ሐገገ (ḥaggaga, “to legislate, to decree”). Perhaps related to حَقَّ (ḥaqqa, “to be right”) and words corresponding to this root in the other Semitic languages, there being for example Hebrew חוק (ḥóqq, “law”)."},"ipa":["/ħad͡ʒ.d͡ʒa/","/ħad͡ʒd͡ʒ/","/ħaɡɡ/","/ħaʒʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7106","headword_ar":"حَجَّ","root":"Hj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He repaired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"betook himself, to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSada","text_ar":"قَصَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) a person (S, A, Mgh) [or place], in an absolute sense: or to, or towards, an object of reverence, veneration, respect, or honour: or, accord. to Kh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he repaired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"betook himself, much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frequently, to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards,"},{"kind":"text","text":"an object of this kind: and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he repaired to, betook himself to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"visited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a person: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"visited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a person"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repeatedly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frequently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, T, S, Mgh, K. *) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~a banuw","text_ar":"حَجَّ بَنُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK fulaAnFA","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sons of such a one continued long going repeatedly to visit such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (S, Mgh, Msb,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (S,) and inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hij~N","text_ar":"حِجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, (Sb, L,) or this is a simple subst., (S, Msb, K,) by a conventional usage, (S,) or predominantly, (Mgh,) or by restriction of its usage in the law, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He repaired to Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the Kaabeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to perform the religious rites and ceremonies of the pilgrimage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the purpose of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eumorap","text_ar":"عُمْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.; but this latter meaning is very rare: the usual meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he performed the pilgrimage to Mekkeh and Mount' Arafát, with all the rites and ceremonies prescribed to be observed at, and between, those two places"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he repaired to the House"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of God, at Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and performed the actions prescribed for that occasion by the law of the Kur-án and the Sunneh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~a Alayota","text_ar":"حَجَّ الَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtj~hu","text_ar":"احتجّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (El-Hejeree, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He performed the pilgrimage to the House"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of God, at Mekkeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, S;) because people repair to it every year. (T, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~uwA mak~apa","text_ar":"حَجُّوا مَكَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They performed the pilgrimage to Mekkeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Haj~a wal`kin~ahu daj~a","text_ar":"مَا حَجَّ وَلٰكِنَّهُ دَجَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did not repair to Mekkeh to visit the House of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Tálib, Az,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the performance of the rites and ceremonies of the pilgrimage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but he journeyed for mercantile purposes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Tálib, Az, Msb. [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dj","text_ar":"دج"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And hence, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laj~a faHaj~a","text_ar":"لَجَّ فَحَجَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a prov., which see below. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrived."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~a EalayonaA fulaAnN","text_ar":"حَجَّ عَلَيْنَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came to us."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also, [aor., accord. to rule, as above,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He shaved"},{"kind":"text","text":"[his head; as one does on completing the performance of the rites and ceremonies of the pilgrimage: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below]. (TA.)       -A3-  Also, (IAar, A, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He probed"},{"kind":"text","text":"a fracture of the head, (K,) or a wound, (A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHojaAj","text_ar":"مِحْجَاج"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyl","text_ar":"مِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the purpose of curing it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he probed"},{"kind":"text","text":"a wound"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to know its depth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he examined"},{"kind":"text","text":"a cleft in the head"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to know whether there were in it bone or blood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he dressed and cured"},{"kind":"text","text":"a wound in the head reaching to the brain: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he poured boiled clarified butter upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"a fracture of the head, in consequence of which the blood was mixed with the brain,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until the blood appeared, which he took away with a little cotton:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~ahu","text_ar":"حَجَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he probed a fracture of his head for the purpose of curing it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made a perforation in the bone"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his broken head"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadaHa fiyhi","text_ar":"قَدَحَ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with an iron instrument, it being broken so that the brain was befouled with blood, and pulled off the skin that had dried up, and then cured it, so that it closed up with a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"new"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it relates to a wound reaching to the brain. (L.) ―         -b2-  Also, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut out and extracted"},{"kind":"text","text":"a bone"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a wound."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A4-  Also, (A, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~u","text_ar":"حَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He overcame"},{"kind":"text","text":"another"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by, an argument, a plea, an alle-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":514},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gation, a proof, an evidence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a testimony."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, K.) See 3. It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laj~a","text_ar":"لَجَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHaj~a","text_ar":"فَحَجَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was pertinacious in litigation, dispute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altercation, and overcame therein"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as is implied in the S, and expressed in the TA]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he persevered until he performed the pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"[not having intended to do so when he set out: see Freytag's “ Arab. Prov. ” ii. 452]. (TA.)       -A5-  Also, (TA,) [aor., accord. to rule,"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~N","text_ar":"حَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajoHaja","text_ar":"حَجْحَجَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajoHajapN","text_ar":"حَجْحَجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He refrained, forbore,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano $aYo'K","text_ar":"عَنْ شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also the latter verb below.]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","Sb","L","T","IAar","ISh"]},{"entry_id":"n7112","headword_ar":"حَجُّ","root":"Hj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hij~N","text_ar":"حِجٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the former an inf. n., and the latter a simple subst., (S, Msb, K,) or the latter also is an inf. n., (Sb, L,) [both used as substs.,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pilgrimage to Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the Kaabeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to perform the religious rites and ceremonies prescribed to be observed on that occasion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) Ks makes no difference between these two words: some say that the former is employed to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religious rites and ceremonies of the pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"because they follow the repairing to Mekkeh, or because they are completed by shaving [the head], or because people continue long going to and fro to perform them: accord. to Az, it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performance of the religious rites and ceremonies of the pilgrimage of one year;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and some say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hij~N","text_ar":"حِجٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hij~apN","text_ar":"حِجَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single pilgrimage, for the performance of its appointed religious rites and ceremonies;"},{"kind":"text","text":"deviating from rule; (S, Mgh, Msb, K;) for by rule it should be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~apN","text_ar":"حَجَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K,) which, Th says, has not been heard from the Arabs: (Mgh, Msb:) Ks says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hajajotu Hij~apF","text_ar":"حَجَجْتُ حِجَّةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^oyapF","text_ar":"رُوْيَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the only deviations from the model of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotu faEolapF","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُ فَعْلَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"in all the language of the Arabs: but El-Athram and others are related to have said, We have not heard from the Arabs"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hajajotu Hij~apF","text_ar":"حَجَجْتُ حِجَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu riy^oyapF","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ رِيْيَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"; they saying only ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hajajotu Haj~apF","text_ar":"حَجَجْتُ حَجَّةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, TA:) whence it appears that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~apN","text_ar":"حَجَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hij~apN","text_ar":"حِجَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"were both used: (TA:) the pl. of the latter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HijajN","text_ar":"حِجَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*ara xamosa HijajK","text_ar":"نَذَرَ خَمْسَ حِجَجٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made a vow to perform five pilgrimages"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) Hence, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw AlHij~api","text_ar":"ذُو الحِجَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*w AlHaj~api","text_ar":"ذو الحَجَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) which latter is said by Kz and 'Iyád and Ibn- Kurkool to be the more common, (TA,) [or, accord. to Fei, the contr. is the case, for he says,] some pronounce it in the latter manner, (Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The last month of the Arabian calendar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the month of the pilgrimage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb;) so called because the pilgrimage to Mekkeh, and the religious rites and ceremonies thereof, are performed in it: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awaAtu AlHj~hi","text_ar":"ذَوَاتُ الحجّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) they did not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awuw AlHaj~pi","text_ar":"ذَوُو الحَجّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with the singular. (S.) [Hence also,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHaj~api","text_ar":"وَحَجَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi laA A^afoEalu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ لَا اَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By the pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the ordinance"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of God, I will not do"},{"kind":"text","text":"this or that thing]: a form of oath used by the Arabs. (S, K.) What is commonly termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~u","text_ar":"الحَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~u AlA^akobaru","text_ar":"الحَجُّ الاَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The greater pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEumorapu","text_ar":"العُمْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] being termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~a","text_ar":"الحَجَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSogaru","text_ar":"الاَصْغَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the minor pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kull p. 168.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAj~N","text_ar":"حَاجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Sb","L","TA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n7113","headword_ar":"حِجُّ","root":"Hj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~u","text_ar":"حَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: ―         -b2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAj~N","text_ar":"حَاجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7253","headword_ar":"حَجٍ","root":"Hjw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajiY~N","text_ar":"حَجِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHajiYN A_ilaY baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَجِىٌ اـِلَى بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA jiy^N lahumo","text_ar":"لَا جِيٌ لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is betaking himself for refuge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protection, to the sons of such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHajiy^N","text_ar":"لَحَجِيٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but by rule it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHajK","text_ar":"لَحَجٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and thus, perhaps, it is correctly written]. (AZ, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}